The angle $P$ is formed by the intersection of these two exterior angles. Since the sum of the angles around a point is 360 degrees, and we have two 60-degree angles, the remaining angle $P$ is:

\begin{align*}
\text{Angle } P &= 360^\circ - (60^\circ + 60^\circ) \\
&= 360^\circ - 120^\circ \\
&= 240^\circ
\end{align*}

However, this is the reflex angle at $P$. The actual angle $P$ is the supplement of this reflex angle, which is:

\begin{align*}
